	<p>After acceptance of our proposal to the client, the analyst uses the system follow-up with a preliminary investigation, which includes a feasibility study. The analyst reviews the client’s business case, considering the company’s overall mission objectives and IT needs. The proposed information system combines information technology, people, and data to support business requirements. Options include Internet-based application services, outsourcing, custom solutions, and enterprise-wide software strategies. The information system identifies five key components: hardware, software, data, processes, and people. 
	</p>
	<p>We design, develop and delivered small-to-large, complete turnkey Information Systems, developed through the entire Software Development Lifecycle (SDLC). This typically includes, analysis, design, test, implementation, deployment, documentation, training, technical support, follow-up, upgrades, conversions, retirement. We have in depth Project Management experience and we can assure you we can be on-time with our deliverables and can base the schedule on your time and convenience. We can include various contract options based on the client’s risks, like Firm-Fixed-Price (FFP), Cost-Plus-Incentive-Fee (CPIF), Cost or Cost-Sharing(C or CS), Time & Materials (T&M) to avoid project overruns and general-schedule accounting for accurate reporting and forecasting to stake-holders.
